about: I am currently a principal at Centerview Partners. I received my MBA from Chicago Booth as part of the class of 2019. Prior to enrolling at Booth, I worked at Capital One for five years across various credit card analytics roles. I obtained my undergraduate degree from Washington University in St. Louis in economics with a minor in general business. While in college, I co-owned and co-operated a small business on campus that provided customized apparel to a wide range of student groups and companies in the St. Louis area.

experience.description:
Description:
Intern at seed-stage venture build company focused on automotive refinance loans. Serving as interim product, finance, and analytics lead during summer internship with responsibilities including:

1) Review of current cash position and forecasted future investment round requirements shared with Managing Partner of venture fund
2) Financial modeling and analytics in preparation of product launch
3) Design product process flow and system controls for tech implementation
4) Collaborate with law firm to draft regulatory policies to establish compliance management system

Strategy and analytics lead for small business card acquisitions across bank branch, industry tradeshows, client development, and affiliate partnerships marketing channels. Key accomplishments included:

1) Deal prioritization, evaluation, and signing of first 25 small business affiliate partnerships
2) Investment and show selection criteria leading to growth of industry tradeshow channel from 40 shows to over 100 shows annually
3) Analytics and oversight into bank channel acquisitions, including audit and regulatory response metrics

Owned business development analytics within Capital One's Small Business Card portfolio. In this role, I identified strategic partnerships that extended the reach of our best-in-class small business credit cards. I also evaluated opportunities to increase the capabilities available to our existing customer base. 

My responsibilities included:
1) Sourcing strategy
2) Deal evaluations
3) Deal negotiations

After my initial role at the company, I transitioned into our card partnerships customer management team. On this team, I initially focused on online capabilities and sizing the potential costs and benefits, both from a financial and customer experience point of view, of adding new functionalities to our customer service platforms.

I then took ownerships for standing up an interactive credit line increase program across our entire partnerships business. After a redesign of our customer communications, process, and credit policy, we saw over 300% growth in response rates to our customer solicitations, with even greater growth in terms of exposure granted to customers.

My first role at Capital One focused on the creation of a new credit card product for our largest cobrand partnerships. I worked along with our partner to create the construct of a best in class value proposition that intends to attract potential high spending cardholders to redeem rewards towards the partner's products. As part of the product redesign, I assisted in the negotiation of a contract extension with the partner. This required my analysis on expected customer performance, acquisition forecasting, and product economics to determine partner compensation terms.

After the product creation, I worked towards the launch of a new acquisitions channel that embedded our application into an existing partner channel and boosted new account volumes by 20%.
Provided custom apparel to many Washington University campus groups along with many corporate customers. Co-owned and co-managed the company for two years before selling it to the current owners.

Worked in the energy and telecom sectors of the US equities portfolio management team. Duties included modeling industry trends and specific companies to identify trading opportunities as well as attending meetings and luncheons with executives from companies deemed potential investments.

Summer intern in the futures and options departments. Company worked out of the New York Mercantile Exchange under the leadership of Richie Schaeffer, former NYMEX chairmen. Focus of investments were in energy futures.

Wrote content for clients at St. Louis based advertising agency. Provided reccomendations on how to improve organic search rankings and then proceeded to implement my reccomendations. Websites I managed saw a noticeable increase in organic rankings.
Worked on Google adwords campaigns and updated and rewrote web content for startup legal directory during their first summer.

Interned under Senior Vice President of Trading at London, England branch of firm. I provided recap on previous day's close to the traders on a daily basis. Accompanied traders in analyst presentations and conference calls and provided research regarding rumors on client's stock.
